{"TopicId":187338,"ForumId":109,"TopicTitle":"KSP2 Hype Train Thread","CreatedByName":"Whirligig Girl","CreatedById":36077,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-19T20:46:45Z","PageNum":153,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T16:47:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226705\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675340439\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA craft situated between them would quickly fall to either side of the system as the point where their gravity is balanced is infinitesimal.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would work like L2 point there web is located the point is unstable but it require little energy to keep in it so web can stay there for a decade using \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nL4 and L5 however is stable so natural material could build up.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tstein","CreatedById":223854,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T16:51:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675356277\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGoldForest was referring to the point directly between Rask and Rusk. So yeah.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow to discuss simulating lagrange zones as small SOIs as a placeholder, well it\u0027s stupid. But I think there\u0027s a clear middleground that\u0027d make everyone happy, continue using rails for most orbits but enable multiple-body gravitation for vessels within zones surrounding the lagrange points. AFAIK, the game should easily be able to figure out where the lagrange zones are for each body and moon. You still get orbital stability but vessels also act in a realistic manner when in proximity to a lagrange point and can hold realistic orbits. Maybe if the player lets a vessels\u0027 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E drain, the game will lock its orbit and keep it in a fixed halo so a player can leave a vessel in a halo orbit without needing to manually keep it there. Sounds similar to SOIs, yeah, but it isn\u0027t; the kind of fixed orbit I propose would use an already-established halo orbit as a basis rather than a weird Keplerian orbit around a black hole that doesn\u0027t behave as an orbit should when it\u0027s being constantly perturbed to form a halo around an imaginary point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo your idea is\u00A0 a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E still, but a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E that has different rules, where conics are replaced by\u00A0 NBody and when you leave that \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E things get into rails again? It still ahs some BLINDNESS to the future (as oen cannot predict the future beign\u00A0 the horizon event of entering or leaving that \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E,\u00A0 but it is a limit that I think\u00A0\u00A0 most players would accept (but need to\u00A0 find a way to explain it because some will get cofnused by that\u00A0 new bermuda triangle in space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T16:56:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675356704\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022223854\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tstein\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, tstein said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo your idea is\u00A0 a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E still, but a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E that has different rules, where conics are replaced by\u00A0 NBody and when you leave that \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E things get into rails again? It still ahs some BLINDNESS to the future (as oen cannot predict the future beign\u00A0 the horizon event of entering or leaving that \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E,\u00A0 but it is a limit that I think\u00A0\u00A0 most players would accept (but need to\u00A0 find a way to explain it because some will get cofnused by that\u00A0 new bermuda triangle in space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think that blindness could be dealt with just by simulating the trajectory a bit ahead like Principia does then continuing patched conics from where the N-body ends.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wouldn\u0027t describe it as a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E because that carries the connotation of a vessel only being affected by one body (and it probably isn\u0027t a sphere), but okay. I\u0027d say \u0022lagrange zone\u0022 would be more apt, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tstein","CreatedById":223854,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T17:09:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226772\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675357003\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think that blindness could be dealt with just by simulating the trajectory a bit ahead like Principia does then continuing patched conics from where the N-body ends.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wouldn\u0027t describe it as a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E because that carries the connotation of a vessel only being affected by one body (and it probably isn\u0027t a sphere), but okay. I\u0027d say \u0022lagrange zone\u0022 would be more apt, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt could work.. the area could be a semi arc segment (with depth )\u00A0 alongside the orbit of a body.\u00A0 It is a reasonable aproximation\u00A0 that allow SOME complex maneuvers\u00A0 yet it does not deeply disrupt long travel planing,\u00A0 not more than\u00A0 entering and leaving a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E already does\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T18:36:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022hidiscord.png?width=1609\u0026amp;height=905\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.42\u0022 height=\u0022674\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1039972362117988353/1070773865917194421/hidiscord.png?width=1609\u0026amp;height=905\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClouds are improving, although some look like hazy mountain peaks. I can see a little bit of layering in the back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nParts look absolutely gorgeous, although there\u0027s some misalignment again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure about the water, kind of looks like ice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOverall I like how the game looks, but the environment needs some more GPU behind it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-02-02T18:39:20Z\u0022 title=\u002202/02/2023 06:39  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 2, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Vl3d\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoldForest","CreatedById":77770,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T18:45:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226806\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675363005\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1039972362117988353/1070773865917194421/hidiscord.png?width=1609\u0026amp;height=905\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022hidiscord.png?width=1609\u0026amp;height=905\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.42\u0022 height=\u0022674\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1039972362117988353/1070773865917194421/hidiscord.png?width=1609\u0026amp;height=905\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClouds are improving, although some look like hazy mountain peaks. I can see a little bit of layering in the back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nParts look absolutely gorgeous, although there\u0027s some misalignment again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure about the water, kind of looks like ice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOverall I like how the game looks, but the environment needs some more GPU behind it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey look like that sometimes IRL.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is months old, they could have probably fixed that issue. The parts weren\u0027t the focus probably when this screenshot was taken.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe\u0027ve only seen the water from far away, up close probably looks good.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey have a set style, so it\u0027s not going to change much.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stephensan","CreatedById":222320,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T18:50:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226806\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675363005\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1039972362117988353/1070773865917194421/hidiscord.png?width=1609\u0026amp;height=905\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022hidiscord.png?width=1609\u0026amp;height=905\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.42\u0022 height=\u0022674\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1039972362117988353/1070773865917194421/hidiscord.png?width=1609\u0026amp;height=905\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClouds are improving, although some look like hazy mountain peaks. I can see a little bit of layering in the back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nParts look absolutely gorgeous, although there\u0027s some misalignment again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure about the water, kind of looks like ice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOverall I like how the game looks, but the environment needs some more GPU behind it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nlook almost clouds, looks frothy, but hope to see them become better.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T18:59:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675363807\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022222320\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Stephensan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Stephensan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nlook almost clouds, looks frothy, but hope to see them become better.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey\u0027re shaving cream. Kerbin has a date tonight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"t_v","CreatedById":213541,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T19:00:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226806\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675363005\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1039972362117988353/1070773865917194421/hidiscord.png?width=1609\u0026amp;height=905\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022hidiscord.png?width=1609\u0026amp;height=905\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.42\u0022 height=\u0022674\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1039972362117988353/1070773865917194421/hidiscord.png?width=1609\u0026amp;height=905\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClouds are improving, although some look like hazy mountain peaks. I can see a little bit of layering in the back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nParts look absolutely gorgeous, although there\u0027s some misalignment again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure about the water, kind of looks like ice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOverall I like how the game looks, but the environment needs some more GPU behind it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the \u201Cmisalignment\u201D is intentional here, if you are talking about the wing tips. The end wing goes past the center one on both the front and the back, so even if the front side was aligned, the back one would go further back. It is more likely that the plane was just designed with big control surfaces.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stephensan","CreatedById":222320,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T19:01:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675364348\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey\u0027re shaving cream. Kerbin has a date tonight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\non god\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Truebadour","CreatedById":141823,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T19:30:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think they look really good considering the cartoony art style of the game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe water shines likes it\u0027s made of metal, but otherwise everything looks really good to me!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-02-02T19:30:15Z\u0022 title=\u002202/02/2023 07:30  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 2, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Truebadour\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T19:36:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ksp-clouds-comparison-3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002253.25\u0022 height=\u0022288\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/NpKD17z/ksp-clouds-comparison-3.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThoughts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stephensan","CreatedById":222320,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T19:50:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226835\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675366579\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/NpKD17z/ksp-clouds-comparison-3.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ksp-clouds-comparison-3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002253.25\u0022 height=\u0022288\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/NpKD17z/ksp-clouds-comparison-3.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThoughts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni mean it does have a long way to go\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pthigrivi","CreatedById":105624,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T19:55:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226839\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675367418\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022222320\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Stephensan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Stephensan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni mean it does have a long way to go\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReally? I think the left already looks better. I mean the two-layers of clouds are cool on the right but the pillow scale is kind of small and repetitive.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ahres","CreatedById":180308,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T19:59:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226840\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675367727\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105624\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pthigrivi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Pthigrivi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReally? I think the left already looks better. I mean the two-layers of clouds are cool on the right but the pillow scale is kind of small and repetitive.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHuh. I think I like the left more as well, honestly.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Truebadour","CreatedById":141823,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T20:06:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe image on the right looks realistic, but that does not really fit the aesthetics of the game imo. Moreover, a really thick layer of clouds hide the ground and I don\u0027t think it\u0027s good for a game like KSP. It looks good but I would find it annoying really quickly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pthigrivi","CreatedById":105624,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T20:15:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd I think if they were to add a high altitude layer it should be wispier like cirrus clouds.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snafu225","CreatedById":143694,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T20:21:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly 20 more days of discussing clouds but here we are \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nLeft just fits better. Right seems somewhat repetitive and like \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/105624-pthigrivi/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022105624\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/105624-pthigrivi/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Pthigrivi\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0already pointed out, the top layer doesn\u0027t feel right.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nNudging this back to on topic hype train:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nI really love that we can see some more verticality to the clouds now and having stock cloud shadows!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T20:31:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m sick of talking about the clouds. They don\u0027t really look like the ones in the Trailer, do they?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ksp-trailer-clouds.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002270.00\u0022 height=\u0022498\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/jMh3N55/ksp-trailer-clouds.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ksp-trailer-clouds-2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002269.75\u0022 height=\u0022499\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/7nbFrk5/ksp-trailer-clouds-2.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stephensan","CreatedById":222320,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T20:32:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226856\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675369292\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022143694\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Snafu225\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Snafu225 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly 20 more days of discussing clouds but here we are \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nLeft just fits better. Right seems somewhat repetitive and like \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/105624-pthigrivi/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022105624\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/105624-pthigrivi/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Pthigrivi\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0already pointed out, the top layer doesn\u0027t feel right.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nNudging this back to on topic hype train:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nI really love that we can see some more verticality to the clouds now and having stock cloud shadows!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhope to see it progress larger and larger.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsoon, soon the ecosystem of the clouds will be here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snafu225","CreatedById":143694,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T20:34:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226863\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675369908\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E7 minutes ago, Vl3d said:\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027m sick of talking about the clouds. They don\u0027t really look like the ones in the Trailer, do they?\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EYet here you are starting the discussion at every possibility and even making comparison pictures.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nEdit: Oh and I didn\u0027t even realise it at first, but since you also posted that in the discord, someone rightfully pointed out that you\u0027re comparing cinematics with ingame graphics.\u00A0\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226864\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675369979\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022222320\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Stephensan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E5 minutes ago, Stephensan said:\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003Ehope to see it progress larger and larger.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003Esoon, soon the ecosystem of the clouds will be here.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EYes, I\u0027m all for the progress they make or maybe even made without us seeing it yet.\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-02-02T20:40:29Z\u0022 title=\u002202/02/2023 08:40  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 2, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Snafu225\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T20:40:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226865\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675370092\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022143694\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Snafu225\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Snafu225 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYet here you are starting the discussion at every possibility and even making comparison pictures.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, because I don\u0027t like seeing clouds that look like a layer of shaving cream PQS terrain.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNeed I remind you?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ksp2-good-kerbin-clouds.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.75\u0022 height=\u0022540\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/SsZ6j1k/ksp2-good-kerbin-clouds.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-02-02T20:43:30Z\u0022 title=\u002202/02/2023 08:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 2, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Vl3d\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WelshSteW","CreatedById":202966,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-02T20:55:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226835\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675366579\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/NpKD17z/ksp-clouds-comparison-3.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ksp-clouds-comparison-3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002253.25\u0022 height=\u0022288\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/NpKD17z/ksp-clouds-comparison-3.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThoughts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe one on the right is better. Forgive my silliness, butis that something you\u0027ve done?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe one on the left looks like they\u0027ve used the terrain tool for the clouds Darn it. They\u0027re just white mountains cut off before they reach the ground. And the water looks crap as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut, again, I guess we don\u0027t know when these were done, or what\u0027s been changed since. I still hold out hope that they\u0027re making it look rubbish so we\u0027re wowed when we actually play and visit the places. My belief in that is dwindling though. Just one shot, just one, where it looks good. Or at least, where it doesn\u0027t look rubbish. Just show us a high res \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, and a bit of surrounding terrain and sky. That wouldn\u0027t be spoilery would it??\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224226866\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221675370409\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, because I don\u0027t like seeing clouds that look like a layer of shaving cream PQS terrain.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNeed I remind you?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/SsZ6j1k/ksp2-good-kerbin-clouds.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ksp2-good-kerbin-clouds.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.75\u0022 height=\u0022540\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/SsZ6j1k/ksp2-good-kerbin-clouds.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis looks promosing? Way better than that left hand pic.\u00A0You could argue this shows clouds, and mist / fog (which I know is really just a cloud as well, but still).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow I don\u0027t know what to think \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-exc